= External Link Template =

{{PRODUCT}} provides the possibility to generate an external link on any wiki page with the help of a [[Template:System:ExternalLink|template]].

== Syntax ==

{| class="wikitable"
!Parameter
!Description
|-
|BaseURL
|Base URL of the link
|-
|Parameter
|Parameter which will be attached to the base URL
|-
|Target
|Target where the link will be opened (_blank (default), _self, _parent, _top) (optional)
|-
|Image
|Image which will be linked (optional)
|-
|Height
|Height of the image (optional)
|-
|Linkname
|Name of the link which will also be used as linktext if no image is provided
|}

== Example ==

=== Example with image ===

In this example a link to the german wikipedia is generated. The label of the current resource is used as parameter. This parameter will be attached to the base URL.
Because the Image parameter is set, the corresponding picture will be shown in the set height.

<source>{{Template:System:ExternalLink
  |BaseURL=https://de.wikipedia.org/wiki/
  |Parameter={{#show: {{this}} | rdfs:label }}
  |Target=_blank
  |Image=https://yt3.ggpht.com/-fFtFQW4BX0w/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/ufTVa6yuX7A/s100-c-k-no-mo-rj-c0xffffff/photo.jpg
  |Height=150
  |Linkname=Semantic Web
}}</source>

{{Template:System:ExternalLink
  |BaseURL=https://de.wikipedia.org/wiki/
  |Parameter=Semantic_Web
  |Target=_blank
  |Image=https://yt3.ggpht.com/-fFtFQW4BX0w/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/ufTVa6yuX7A/s100-c-k-no-mo-rj-c0xffffff/photo.jpg
  |Height=150
  |Linkname=Semantic Web
}}

=== Example with linktext ===

In this example a link to the german wikipedia is generated. The label of the current resource is used as parameter. This parameter will be attached to the base URL.
Because the Image parameter is not set, the Linkname will be used as linktext.


<source>{{Template:System:ExternalLink
  |BaseURL=https://de.wikipedia.org/wiki/
  |Parameter=Semantic_Web
  |Target=_blank
  |Linkname=Semantic Web
}}</source>

{{Template:System:ExternalLink
  |BaseURL=https://de.wikipedia.org/wiki/
  |Parameter=Semantic_Web
  |Target=_blank
  |Linkname=Semantic Web
}}